Lincoln City sign striker Bradley Barraclough
Barraclough recently completed a university scholarship in the USA
Lincoln City have signed striker Bradley Barraclough, 22, on a one-year deal after he impressed in pre-season.Barraclough grew up in Lincolnshire and played for the county at junior level. He earned a trial after posting a video of his goals for Bellarmine University Knights in the USA, where he had a scholarship, on the internet. Imps manager Steve Tilson told BBC Lincolnshire: "He's really keen, he works his socks off and I think he'll be a good addition to the squad." Bookmark with: Delicious Digg reddit Facebook StumbleUpon What are these?
